    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <head>291. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    Station in Saigon to the <gloss type="to">Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d291fn1">Source: National Defense University,
                            <persName corresp="#p_TGMD1">Taylor</persName> Papers, T-172-69. Top
                        Secret. There is no telegram number indicated on the source text.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1963-08-26">August 26, 1963</date>
                        </hi>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Colonel Conein spoke with General <persName corresp="#p_TTKG1">Tran Thien
                            Khiem</persName> approximately 1245 hours local and reviewed points
                        contained [<hi rend="italic">document number not declassified</hi>] (IN
                            06507).<note n="2" xml:id="d291fn2">
                            <ref target="#d290">Document 290</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>General <persName corresp="#p_KHIEM1">Khiem</persName> replied as follows: <list>
                            <label>a.</label>
                            <item>Generals were in accord with points expressed. Pleased to know US
                                position.</item>
                            <label>b.</label>
                            <item>These points should not be raised with General <persName
                                    corresp="#p_TVDMG1">Tran Van Don</persName> at this time since
                                    <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> has certain officers
                                on General <persName corresp="#p_DON1">Don</persName>’s staff and
                                might become aware of this from them.</item>
                            <label>c.</label>
                            <item>Colonel Conein should stand by for later pickup by jeep by an
                                officer sent by General <persName corresp="#p_KHIEM1"
                                    >Khiem</persName>. This jeep will take Colonel Conein to
                                immediate future meeting with General <persName corresp="#p_DVMG1"
                                    >Duong Van Minh</persName>.</item>
                            <label>d.</label>
                            <item>General <persName corresp="#p_KHIEM1">Khiem</persName> concurred
                                in contact with General <persName corresp="#p_KHANH1"
                                    >Khanh</persName> by [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                                    declassified</hi>] on these points and stated that he would
                                inform General <persName corresp="#p_KHANH1">Khanh</persName> by
                                secure means available to him that he is aware of [<hi rend="italic"
                                    >less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] mission and in
                                agreement with it.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
